I like this place. The first time I came here I had a nice ramen and sushi roll. It was for dinner mind you. The quality was decent, it was close to my place, and the cost was fairly inexpensive, so overall a nice place to visit and I'm glad I found it. When I came here for lunch, I found out they did all-you-can-eat, which ends up being pretty amazing. You fill out a card indicating how much you want of what, they bring it to you, and then they give you another card for rounds 2 through infinite. While the quality of the food during all-you-can-eat suffers a bit (especially the broth for the ramen), the cost is pretty crazy in a good way.  This isn't a top-notch Japanese restaurant and I don't think they try to be. But for the price, it really is a great place to go.

Portion Sizes are a little overboard, but if you're going with friends it's definetly a go to spot for sushi. I didn't have that much time to explore the other dishes but from the dishes I ordered the eel nigiri is definetly the best thing I ordered, it was nicely cooked and the fat from the eel just covered the rice and it flavored it. The eel nigiri just melted in your mouth, fabulous.  I also ordered chicken katsu, the portion size was just too much for me to handle haha, but like I said from the beginning if you have some friends it's a nice place to go. The taste of the chicken katsu tasted alot like chicken nuggets from any fast food restaurant, definetly not my style but the katsu itself was super crispy which is a plus. The sauce that was given to go along with the katsu had a very Heinz tomato ketchup flavor which is also not my style all in all the eel was the spotlight.  Good place to get a quick sushi and very affordable but I would stay away from the dishes that is not sushi, hence the name sushi factory which specializes in sushi rather then other dishes 4/5.
